1
00:00:02,520 --> 00:00:03,690
That guy Fukami...

2
00:00:04,080 --> 00:00:06,470
He just woke up and
left like it was nothing.

3
00:00:07,370 --> 00:00:09,390
Still as cold as ever.

4
00:00:11,190 --> 00:00:12,210
Good morning.

5
00:00:12,670 --> 00:00:13,670
Morning.

6
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:15,930
Thanks for taking care of me on Friday.

7
00:00:21,490 --> 00:00:22,490
Um...

8
00:00:22,580 --> 00:00:23,760
I'm sorry, who are you?

9
00:00:27,950 --> 00:00:29,150
What are you talking about?

10
00:00:29,640 --> 00:00:30,640
Wait...

11
00:00:30,839 --> 00:00:31,839
Fukami?

12
00:00:34,070 --> 00:00:36,070
The Fukami I know
at the office is always...

13
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:37,880
So dorky.

14
00:00:37,950 --> 00:00:38,950
He wears glasses,

15
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:40,040
and he's so gloomy.

16
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:42,800
He looks so... polished.

17
00:00:43,590 --> 00:00:44,590
Wh...

18
00:00:44,590 --> 00:00:45,590
What happened to you?

19
00:00:47,620 --> 00:00:49,030
What's with the new look?

20
00:00:52,540 --> 00:00:54,620
Well, it's been a while
since I went out for drinks,

21
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:58,510
so I thought I should try to look decent.

22
00:00:59,870 --> 00:01:02,310
But I have no fashion sense,

23
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:05,200
so I asked my sister for help,
and she got a bit carried away.

24
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:08,250
She really went all out.

25
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:11,410
You're like a completely different person.

26
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,460
It's weird, isn't it?

27
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:17,790
Maybe I should at least
put my glasses back on.

28
00:01:18,930 --> 00:01:20,060
No, it's not weird.

29
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:21,750
It's really not.

30
00:01:22,210 --> 00:01:23,250
But in a moment like this,

31
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,920
I honestly don't know what to say.

32
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:27,620
Good work. I can't get a hold of that guy.

33
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,980
Wait, seriously?

34
00:01:29,180 --> 00:01:30,740
Good morning, Kaji-san.

35
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:32,570
- Morning.
- What are you doing?

36
00:01:32,620 --> 00:01:35,070
- Just taking a break.
- Which department are you in?

37
00:01:36,690 --> 00:01:38,190
I'm in Tech.

38
00:01:38,682 --> 00:01:39,846
What year did you join the company?

39
00:01:39,870 --> 00:01:41,710
Sorry if this is forward,
but are you married?

40
00:01:41,870 --> 00:01:43,370
No, I'm not.

41
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:46,056
Are you on Instagram or anything?

42
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:48,440
Fukami is suddenly very popular.

43
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,599
"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami"

44
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:52,500
- I'm Fukami.
- Fukami-san, right?

45
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,750
Oh, can I get your LINE?

46
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:59,560
(Episode 4)
Is there something wrong with the system?

47
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:01,470
No, I haven't heard anything.

48
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:04,290
Weren't there a ton of
people in Tech just now?

49
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,480
Oh, yeah.

50
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:06,880
That's pretty unusual.

51
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Tell me about it.

52
00:02:10,420 --> 00:02:13,210
Hey, that guy is Fukami-san, right?

53
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:15,480
- He's so cute.
- Totally.

54
00:02:16,530 --> 00:02:18,030
I wonder if he has a girlfriend.

55
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:19,569
Let's go ask him.

56
00:02:19,570 --> 00:02:20,570
Go ask...

57
00:02:27,780 --> 00:02:29,330
Fukami is "cute"?

58
00:02:29,626 --> 00:02:30,626
No.

59
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:32,370
You guys have no idea.

60
00:02:34,550 --> 00:02:37,050
Like how he'll suddenly
laugh at the weirdest times.

61
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:39,280
When I'm with you,

62
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:41,370
I feel like I'm not myself anymore.

63
00:02:43,770 --> 00:02:45,570
Or how aggressive he gets when he's drunk.

64
00:02:45,730 --> 00:02:47,030
Is this not okay?

65
00:02:48,180 --> 00:02:50,400
I'm already getting a little hard.

66
00:02:53,530 --> 00:02:54,530
All those sides of him...

67
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,550
They're supposed to be my secret.

68
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:01,700
Hypothetically.

69
00:03:01,780 --> 00:03:02,950
Just thinking out loud here.

70
00:03:06,870 --> 00:03:08,440
Even though it would never happen.

71
00:03:09,850 --> 00:03:10,950
If I...

72
00:03:11,130 --> 00:03:13,370
If I actually fell for him.

73
00:03:16,510 --> 00:03:18,590
Didn't I tell you not
to fall in love with me?

74
00:03:19,150 --> 00:03:20,150
We should...

75
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,820
stop being friends with benefits.

76
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,300
No way, no way.

77
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:30,870
It'd be such a waste to give up that body.

78
00:03:34,090 --> 00:03:35,520
What if he...

79
00:03:36,210 --> 00:03:37,410
What if he fell for me?

80
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:44,330
I've fallen for you.

81
00:03:45,230 --> 00:03:46,360
But it's too much trouble.

82
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:48,020
Let's not see each other anymore.

83
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:53,700
That's a possibility.

84
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:56,420
Then...

85
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:57,940
What if the feeling was mutual?

86
00:04:06,260 --> 00:04:08,670
That's a total mystery.
I can't even imagine it.

87
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,720
Besides,

88
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:14,160
I've never had that kind
of relationship with anyone.

89
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:17,220
Our personalities are too different.

90
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:19,540
I don't think it would work out.

91
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:23,420
So then,

92
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:25,670
this thing we have...

93
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,000
How long will it last?

94
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:34,060
How far will it go?

95
00:04:44,165 --> 00:04:46,165
(Mr. Zero: I'm free on Friday)

96
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:47,780
He's the one asking to meet.

97
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:49,470
That's a first.

98
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:53,590
What does "I'm free" even mean?

99
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:56,390
He should be saying,

100
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,050
"Please see me."

101
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:01,020
When he's alone,

102
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:04,000
does he think about sleeping with me too?

103
00:05:18,390 --> 00:05:20,050
I'm making coffee.

104
00:05:20,190 --> 00:05:21,190
Want some?

105
00:05:22,230 --> 00:05:23,290
Oh.

106
00:05:24,910 --> 00:05:25,910
No, I'm good.

107
00:05:27,350 --> 00:05:28,840
The shower's all yours.

108
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:30,590
I already showered at home.

109
00:05:36,140 --> 00:05:37,470
You're back to your old self.

110
00:05:39,570 --> 00:05:40,770
I don't know...

111
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:43,050
I couldn't really relax.

112
00:05:45,930 --> 00:05:47,030
I'm relieved.

113
00:05:48,420 --> 00:05:50,380
The side of him I don't
want anyone else to know.

114
00:05:53,340 --> 00:05:54,990
The way his messy hair

115
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:56,940
clings to the back of his neck.

116
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:00,900
I guess...

117
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:02,590
I actually kind of like it.

118
00:06:17,370 --> 00:06:18,580
Hey, you're gonna make me spill!

119
00:06:24,660 --> 00:06:25,660
You...

120
00:06:25,910 --> 00:06:27,430
You're pretty popular now, aren't you?

121
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,560
Wait...

122
00:06:30,350 --> 00:06:31,800
Am I?

123
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:35,450
Don't play dumb after all that attention.

124
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:37,130
And then,

125
00:06:37,180 --> 00:06:38,460
put your hands behind your back.

126
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,040
Like this...

127
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:50,620
Wait a second.

128
00:06:51,170 --> 00:06:52,300
Stop it.

129
00:06:52,690 --> 00:06:54,000
What is this even for?

130
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:56,580
I love the way you're
looking at me right now.

131
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,070
I'm not into this kind of thing.

132
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:02,830
That's not what it looks like.

133
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:05,730
Your body is being pretty honest.

134
00:07:09,340 --> 00:07:10,570
I said stop.

135
00:07:11,670 --> 00:07:13,180
That hurts.

136
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:15,059
Didn't you say last time

137
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:16,786
to just tell you if there was
something I wanted to do?

138
00:07:16,810 --> 00:07:17,330
Huh?

139
00:07:17,331 --> 00:07:18,620
I never said that.

140
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:20,890
Yes, you did.

141
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,790
Don't you remember, you drunk?

142
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:25,990
Shut up and untie me.

143
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:29,060
Let me take the lead for once.

144
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,380
As long as you don't hurt me,

145
00:08:00,430 --> 00:08:01,690
I guess it's okay.

146
00:08:12,430 --> 00:08:14,350
I would never hurt you.

147
00:08:25,430 --> 00:08:26,430
Is this jealousy?

148
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,510
Or just possessiveness?

149
00:08:38,290 --> 00:08:40,070
The Fukami only I get to see.

150
00:08:45,850 --> 00:08:47,390
I want to touch you in the front.

151
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,660
Untie me.

152
00:08:51,860 --> 00:08:52,860
Kaji.

153
00:08:55,270 --> 00:08:57,100
No.

154
00:08:58,810 --> 00:09:00,010
The only thing you're allowed to use

155
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:01,270
is my body.

156
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:04,560
Help me...

157
00:09:06,990 --> 00:09:08,360
Please.

158
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:10,490
Even when I make him look like that,

159
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:12,940
the one who's really in control

160
00:09:13,710 --> 00:09:15,460
is always him.

161
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,970
When I'm with this guy,

162
00:09:25,390 --> 00:09:27,260
I can't keep my cool at all.

163
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:33,040
I overdid it again.

164
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,240
Why does it always

165
00:09:37,950 --> 00:09:39,440
end up like this?

166
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,120
Are you okay?

167
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:28,250
Is something wrong?

168
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,160
Huh?

169
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,970
Don't "huh" me!

170
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:36,020
You seem like your mind is elsewhere.

171
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,040
If you're not feeling it,

172
00:10:39,650 --> 00:10:41,960
don't force yourself. You can say no.

173
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:46,980
Who's fault do you think that is?

174
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,400
It's because you're always

175
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:53,640
messing with

176
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:55,080
my head!

177
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,870
Do you think I just come running

178
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:01,190
every time you ask to meet?

179
00:11:01,730 --> 00:11:02,730
Wait, what?

180
00:11:03,450 --> 00:11:06,000
I'm not here because you asked.

181
00:11:06,830 --> 00:11:08,280
I just wanted to do it myself.

182
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:10,660
You just happened to message me,

183
00:11:10,810 --> 00:11:12,300
and you were convenient.

184
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:18,140
Stop acting like you know me.

185
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:21,460
What do you even know about me?

186
00:11:21,930 --> 00:11:23,930
We've only slept together
a few times, haven't we?

187
00:11:26,460 --> 00:11:27,460
Well,

188
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:29,270
I guess that's true.

189
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,320
Hey.

190
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,940
Let's stop seeing each other for a while.

191
00:11:42,940 --> 00:11:44,040
I understand.

192
00:11:58,820 --> 00:11:59,920
In the past,

193
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,900
whenever things got complicated,

194
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,720
I'd just cut ties immediately.

195
00:12:09,580 --> 00:12:11,860
It's just a casual game
to satisfy my urges.

196
00:12:18,490 --> 00:12:19,800
Block them,

197
00:12:20,190 --> 00:12:21,760
pretend they never existed,

198
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:23,950
and move on to the next one.

199
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:29,790
Dammit.

200
00:12:30,770 --> 00:12:32,480
It always worked before.

201
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:34,420
It was always so easy...

202
00:12:35,330 --> 00:12:37,520
How long is "for a while" supposed to be?

203
00:12:38,990 --> 00:12:40,190
Dammit!

204
00:12:45,090 --> 00:12:46,090
Promise me...

205
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:48,600
that you'll never fall in love with me.

206
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:55,270
If you're so worried
about me falling for you,

207
00:12:55,730 --> 00:12:58,660
you shouldn't have been so kind to me.

208
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,510
(Next Episode)
I have a high fever.

209
00:13:02,590 --> 00:13:04,130
Kaji-kun seems to have a high fever.

210
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:05,470
Let him get some rest.

211
00:13:05,990 --> 00:13:08,020
I'm surprised you invited me over.

212
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,656
(Mr. Zero: I'm nearby. Are you home?)

213
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:12,490
Zero... so you're that "Mr. Zero."

214
00:13:12,890 --> 00:13:15,060
I should've never slept
with you in the first place.
